<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>\(p\) is a prime number such that its remainder divided by 8 is 3. Find all pairs of rational numbers \((x,y)\) that satisfy the following equation.
\[p^2 x^4-6px^2+1=y^2\]</p>
